cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the implementation of channel bonding in cognitive radio sensor networks, which involves the use of wireless communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with the issue of interference and data rate requirements, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes intelligent channel bonding schemes, which involve the use of algorithms and decision-making processes, making it relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the need for stable channels, which can be considered as a control system, making it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which can be considered as a multimedia application, making it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
